        <p>
          Metropolis Light Transport (MLT) is an algorithm for solving image lighting problems. MLT generates a sequence of light-carrying paths through the image and, where each path is found by manipulating the previous path to some degree. MLT consists of two phases. First, a <i>bidirectional</i> path tracer is used to generate an initial population of light transport paths. Second, each initial path is mutated in turn and each manipulation is either accepted or rejected with a probability. Finally, each pathâ€™s contribution are then recorded on the image plane.
